            <scopecontent id="aspace_0c9a91a4d5f6050a9eac48546d2a29d1">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>The Edward A. Bayne Papers consist of correspondence and articles written by E. A. Bayne, former member of the American University Field Staff, and by Somali writer, Yousuf Duhul. The materials pertain to Somali government activities circa the late 1950s through the early 1960s and in particular with Mohammed Abshir Mussa, former commandant of the Somali national police, released in 1982 after twelve years as a political prisoner.</p>
            </scopecontent>
